In an impl block:
```rust
impl Foo {
    fn new() -> NotAFoo {
    }
}
```

```rust
struct Bar(Foo);
impl Foo {
    // Bad. The type name must contain `Self`
    fn new() -> Bar {
    }
}
```

```rust
impl Foo {
    // Good. Return type contains `Self`
    fn new() -> Result<Foo, FooError> {
    }
}
```

Or in a trait definition:
```rust
pub trait Trait {
    // Bad. The type name must contain `Self`
    fn new();
}
```

```rust
pub trait Trait {
    // Good. Return type contains `Self`
    fn new() -> Self;
}
```

```ignore
struct Foo(Bar);

impl Foo {
    fn new() -> Self {
        Foo(Bar::new())
    }
}
```

To fix the lint, add a `Default` implementation that delegates to `new`:

```ignore
struct Foo(Bar);

impl Default for Foo {
    fn default() -> Self {
        Foo::new()
    }
}
```

